HEADWORD: Hibernacle
<hw>Hi*ber"na*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>hibernaculum</ets> a winter residence, pl. <ets>hibernacula</ets>
winter quarters: cf. F. <ets>hibernacle</ets>. See
<er>Hibernate</er>.]</ety> <def>That which serves for protection or
shelter in winter; winter quarters; <as>as, the <ex>hibernacle</ex> of
an animal or a plant</as>.</def> <rj><au>Martyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

